data.name: Indication1.ToolTip
data.value: Enter the name of the rung that triggers the graphic. The color box beside the indication name is color the graphic will be drawn. Place a tilde (~) in front of the function name to invert logic. If multiple graphics are selected at the same time, either a "?" is if the items are different, or if they are the same the name will show. eg. "~13HR" will trigger when the function 13HR is low.

data.name: AngleBox.ToolTip
data.value: Enter the rotation angle in degrees of the graphic. (ie. 0-360 degrees). Starts at the 3 0'clock position and sweeps anticlockwise. 0 degrees equates to the 3 o'clock position, 90 degrees equates to 12 0'clock, 180 degrees equates to 9 o'clock, 270 degrees equates to 6 o'clock.
